80 grams Green Beans
125 grams Egg Noodle Nest
240 grams British Beef Mince
120 grams Coleslaw Mix
64 grams Hoisin Sauce
1 sachet(s) Szechuan Paste
48 grams Sweet Chilli Sauce
50 milliliter(s) Water for the Sauce

Boil a half-full kettle.
Meanwhile, trim the green beans. Cut into thirds.
Pour the boiled water into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the noodles, 4 mins. Once cooked, drain and run under cold water.

Meanwhile, heat a frying pan on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, fry the beef and green beans, 5-6 mins.
Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Next, add the coleslaw to the pan. Stir-fry, 2-3 mins.
Stir in the hoisin, Szechuan, sweet chilli and water (see pantry).
Bring to the boil. Simmer, 1-2 mins. Season with salt and pepper.
Add the cooked noodles. Toss to coat in the sauce, 1 min. Add a splash of water if needed.

Share the beef noodles between your bowls.
Enjoy!